to redd, the drapp cullours in said bale N. 9 are good, where fore provide
6 peeces more of the same ccll. & leverall prijses as also one or2
chore as N. 578: with 4 more of the inclosed patt to make up an
other bale of spanish cabathes, butt not exceeding 10 s ayd viz from
6 st to 10 ayd I want most low prijses the blews are some what
to darck where fore provide 2 more some what lighter & add

bale for northren goods you shall have orders p. next. the cottons must
be orderedas by my last ½ in one bale and about the cottons 8 a9
salempores in each ½ cotton att furthest & wrap pered with 2 bayes
onely butt the bayes must be thrned round abrutt the cottons
& not so much under or above, because the changes should see the
lest the cettons, lett each ½ cotton by stuckt with 3 ropes imsteed
of 2on boath sides, that so the lists are closed the better

In Antwerpen 31 mars 81
Gent francois Herrebout
Mons. in antwoort aen ul van 29 deser de 2 packen N. 10 & 37 fijn van brugge adroit ur
gesonden, ul soude geirne op sicht op mij ƒ 200:- treken, ul gelieft mijn voriger
Rek. te senden en tgeene ul komt tot uld. eb lest leden sal betalen, maer tis
mijn contentement niet deen jaer int ander te laten loopen, oversulx sent mij
de Rek tot daer toe gesloten volgens voor desen geseijt, en dat ul p slot daer van
sal komen, sal geirne opsicht betalen, hope sondagh bij ul te wesen blijve

In Antwerp m aprill
S in answer to yd of 30t past do inclosed remitt you £500 att the charge of
of will scawen of 28 past dubble uso which lost 35:7 I could do itt not other
wise & is accordingly as I have don this day for my self, so please to note according
I have recd our seges & silk hose, the latter sold & the serges supose toturne &
of speedly, I could have wished more gold & black mode mixtcollours had
ben amonghst them the goods out of nelson are also arrived & att our
meeting shall give you my opinion, the ham brough buyng doth finish
31 past which is thcuritt when itt is time for us to beginne, the
meetiny please will be the usuall un less you would have itt other wise
I intend to so with the waggon on saturday morning to he you the
same night god willing, for the following mimday must & here againe
I shall bring the needfull acctt. with mee & exspect from you the hake
as to in Herreford the notary which hath the papers in handes is sich
which will retard the cause some dayes yett shall endeavour to bring
mee
the answer with mee & so remanne
